01:02:38.799 --> 01:02:43.790
And the loudest people in the section are usually the ones doing nothing for Him at all.

01:02:43.791 --> 01:02:51.281
And they yell at the people who are trying their hardest, and they have the big 'L'sign on the side: "You're a loser.

01:02:51.282 --> 01:02:58.227
You've got nothing going for you."And you look at them and go, "But what did you do this year?

01:02:58.228 --> 01:03:11.039
How many people did you lead to Christ this year? How many people did you pray for?"And all the criticism from the peanut gallery—shut up.

01:03:11.040 --> 01:03:16.415
You know, we're all trying. The ones that are trying, keep trying.

01:03:16.416 --> 01:03:29.439
I knew whenever the Lord was talking to me about the stripes—"By His stripes, you are healed."Fall down on the concrete and skin your knee.

01:03:29.440 --> 01:03:39.142
And how bad does that hurt? It's excruciating for somebody, especially if you're elderly, and you just take all the skin off.

01:03:39.143 --> 01:03:44.873
Imagine having a cat o'nine tails whipping your back and tearing that flesh off.

01:03:44.874 --> 01:03:54.623
He went through it all for you to live in victory. That wasn't a skinned knee, as bad as that hurts.

01:03:54.624 --> 01:03:59.199
You can picture that, can't you? What if you pinch yourself and it's really real?

01:03:59.200 --> 01:04:04.893
It hurts a little bit whenever you maybe stuck your hand in the car door or something and it hurts really bad.

01:04:04.894 --> 01:04:16.871
Jesus went through hell for every single one of us. More than just a skinned knee. More than just a hand in the car door.

01:04:16.872 --> 01:04:31.565
I remember one time my dad was working as a carpenter using a nail gun and he was putting the nail in the air gun and it went through his hand.

01:04:31.566 --> 01:04:41.229
His buddy Tommy had to take a crowbar and pull my dad's hand off of that board, if I remember correctly.

01:04:41.230 --> 01:04:45.668
He had to hold it because he couldn't get the blood on the wood because they were finishing it.

01:04:45.669 --> 01:04:51.201
So, his hand had to be pried off of the wood and the blood was trying to squirt all over the place.

01:04:51.202 --> 01:04:57.038
They grabbed it and had to wrap it in a cloth because they didn't want to stain the oak wood because they were working on really expensive houses.

01:04:57.039 --> 01:05:07.170
And it was excruciating. But Jesus took nails, big humongous nails. I saw the holes in His hand.

01:05:07.171 --> 01:05:20.083
This isn't something that's just some kind of fairy tale that we read to our kids before we go to sleep, like Goldilocks and the Three Bears or Little Red Riding Hood.

01:05:20.084 --> 01:05:30.930
Jesus Christ died for you, and it's not some fairy tale. He went through it just like when you skin your knee and you go through pain and it's excruciating.

01:05:30.931 --> 01:05:37.038
Jesus Christ took it all on His back and they ripped His flesh off His body and they put nails in His hands.

01:05:37.039 --> 01:05:44.159
They put a crown of thorns on His head. They ripped His beard out. They spat in His face.

01:05:44.160 --> 01:05:51.199
They hung Him on a cross and they shoved a spear in His side and blood and water flowed.

01:05:51.200 --> 01:05:59.598
A massive gash was in His side. He suffered greatly for you to walk in victory.

01:05:59.599 --> 01:06:17.838
I'll never forget one night I was sitting on the side of a bed—I know I'm going a little long but you need to hear it—I was talking to a man that was really overcoming arthritis and he said, "Brandon, how come all Christians aren't healed?

01:06:17.839 --> 01:06:21.432
Why aren't all Christians healed, Brandon? I don't understand.

01:06:21.433 --> 01:06:25.999
I've been suffering with this arthritis so bad."His name was Stanley.

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:30.790
His hand was always hurting with arthritis, and he couldn't understand why all Christians aren't healed.

01:06:30.791 --> 01:06:40.719
I said, "I don't know. I don't have the answer to it."I laid down, went to bed, and I was taken out of my body.

01:06:40.720 --> 01:06:54.798
Jesus took me to the cross. He took me to the whipping post. I can tell you the temperature that it was outside: it was about 80 degrees.

01:06:54.799 --> 01:07:04.770
It had a stench in the atmosphere. I could smell some kind of animal livestock dung where He was at. I don't know how, but I could smell it.

01:07:04.771 --> 01:07:17.038
Jesus was standing right here—now, He was sitting right here—but I was watching Jesus in the past as a young man of 33 years old.

01:07:17.039 --> 01:07:22.158
His hands were tied to this whipping post. He was straddled up on this.

01:07:22.159 --> 01:07:30.078
And I saw Him up like this. And I saw one Roman soldier on one side and another one on this side.

01:07:30.079 --> 01:07:37.195
I watched both of those men. One man was probably 300 pounds. He was ginormous.

01:07:37.196 --> 01:07:45.547
He had a totally black outfit on, which I don't understand—that's what it looked like, some kind of weird garment.

01:07:45.548 --> 01:07:53.919
But the other was a Roman soldier that had Roman garb on like you would see in the movies.

01:07:53.920 --> 01:08:02.287
And I saw them take the cat o'nine tails and one whipped this side and the other one whipped this side.

01:08:02.288 --> 01:08:11.199
And as I saw that happen, I saw the flesh ripping off of His body and it was excruciating.

01:08:11.200 --> 01:08:22.541
It was dripping from His body—the bone, everything. It was the most grotesque thing I've ever seen.

01:08:22.542 --> 01:08:29.498
I saw the crown of thorns upon His head pressed down and blood was running down His forehead.

01:08:29.499 --> 01:08:37.198
His beard was missing pieces where they had ripped the beard out of His face.

01:08:37.199 --> 01:08:47.201
I remember I was standing over here as I was watching this happen and I was weeping and I was screaming but nobody could hear me and I said, "Stop!

01:08:47.202 --> 01:08:53.055
You must stop!"and I was screaming because they were beating Him with those whips.

01:08:53.056 --> 01:09:10.158
They were whipping His body and His body would tremble as they were whipping His body and the blood was so much on the ground it was like He was in a pool of blood.

01:09:10.159 --> 01:09:26.314
As they did it, I saw Jesus look up and I saw Him, out of His mouth, tell that one soldier, "I love you. I love you."I saw it.

01:09:26.315 --> 01:09:40.959
His face looked up at him and it was the most sincere look in His eyes as they were laughing and they were beating His body.

01:09:40.960 --> 01:09:44.359
Jesus was standing beside me over here as I watched this all happen.

01:09:44.360 --> 01:09:48.718
I can even tell you what His back looked like before they beat Him.

01:09:48.719 --> 01:09:58.399
He was not skinny looking; He was muscular looking. His skin looked olive. It looked glossy from oily sweat.

01:09:58.400 --> 01:10:06.359
You know how whenever you sweat and you get that oil on your body from not having a bath in a little bit?

01:10:06.360 --> 01:10:16.718
That's the way His back looked before they began. I watched it.

01:10:16.719 --> 01:10:30.479
The Lord spoke to me that day and He said to me, "What do you not understand about 'by My stripes you are healed,'Brandon?

01:10:30.480 --> 01:10:47.919
What do you not understand about this?"He said, "If somebody was to tell you that you weren't saved, that you weren't born again, you would fight them, wouldn't you?

01:10:47.920 --> 01:10:56.718
You would tell them, 'I am saved.'If they say, 'I don't believe you're saved,'you'd say, 'I am saved. I am delivered.

01:10:56.719 --> 01:11:11.119
I know He saved my soul by what He did for me.'"But the moment you feel sickness and disease, you doubt that you're healed.

01:11:11.120 --> 01:11:19.336
He said, "The same faith that it takes to get healed is the same faith that it takes to be saved.

01:11:19.337 --> 01:11:39.279
They're the same."He said, "You don't realize what it takes for you to say, 'I was once lost, but now I'm found.

01:11:39.280 --> 01:11:48.238
I'm no longer going to hell.'You don't look at the miracle that truly is.

01:11:48.239 --> 01:11:57.009
But the same faith that you would fight somebody by telling them, 'I know I'm saved.'"They say, "No, I don't believe it.

01:11:57.010 --> 01:11:59.924
You still act the way you used to sometimes. I don't believe it.

01:11:59.925 --> 01:12:04.300
Are you really saved?""No, I know I'm saved. I'm going to heaven.

01:12:04.301 --> 01:12:18.750
I'm not going to hell."He said it takes the same faith to sit there and say, "I'm healed by Your stripes, Lord."He said, "When you believe that the same way, Brandon, the manifestation comes as long as you hold on to it just like that.

01:12:18.751 --> 01:12:25.874
No matter if they talk you out of it. 'I have a symptom, Lord. I have a symptom. My flesh is crying out. I've got this pain in my body.

01:12:25.875 --> 01:12:35.353
I've got this going on.'But it's the same way the pain of the soul is whenever you are messing up with sin and you have that, but you don't question your mind because of the symptom of it.

01:12:35.354 --> 01:12:38.873
I'm saved. I believe. I'm once saved, always saved. Don't you know that?

01:12:38.874 --> 01:12:44.011
Well, I'm once healed, always healed. I'm healed and whole and well.

01:12:44.012 --> 01:12:50.610
By His stripes, I am healed. He was wounded for my transgressions. He was bruised for my iniquities.

01:12:50.611 --> 01:12:57.759
The chastisement of my peace was upon Him, and with His stripes, I am healed.

01:12:57.760 --> 01:13:05.895
He said, 'I became poor that you might be rich through My poverty. I took poverty on the cross, Brandon. I took it all.

01:13:05.896 --> 01:13:17.678
Christ has redeemed me from the curse of the law.'Galatians 3:13, Christ has redeemed me from the curse of the law.

01:13:17.679 --> 01:13:22.436
Deuteronomy 28 says there are a lot of curses there at the very end of that.

01:13:22.438 --> 01:13:31.193
And all those curses, if you don't know, you can partake in them just like you partake in the blessing.

01:13:31.194 --> 01:13:37.662
But Jesus paid the price so you don't have to. He became sickness.

01:13:37.663 --> 01:13:49.091
He became poor. He became sin. He took it all for us so that we don't have to.

01:13:49.092 --> 01:13:57.759
And that's when he said, 'You so easily believe in salvation. The body of Christ has got that down.

01:13:57.760 --> 01:14:03.755
But you must believe that I'm a healer just as much as I'm a redeemer.

01:14:03.756 --> 01:14:08.037
I take you out of hell. I've done all this, but I can heal your body, too.

01:14:08.038 --> 01:14:18.596
But you must believe it.'It shook me. Oh, I don't believe that, Brandon.

01:14:18.597 --> 01:14:27.839
It's what I saw. It's what I experienced as I went back into my body.

01:14:27.840 --> 01:14:33.359
For three days, I wept. I called my dad even that same morning. I wept.

01:14:33.360 --> 01:14:41.279
I couldn't control myself because of what I saw Jesus go through.

01:14:41.280 --> 01:14:47.439
Jesus paid the price for you to walk in victory over mental torment.

01:14:47.440 --> 01:15:02.027
Jesus paid the price for you to walk in victory over depression, over anxiety, over fear, over all the things that the devil tries to. Don't accept the poo-poo package the devil has for you.

01:15:02.028 --> 01:15:13.759
When he comes with his FedEx truck and he has 'the devil'written on it, don't accept his package through sickness, disease, poverty, sin, whatever he has.

01:15:13.760 --> 01:15:22.791
Shut the door to the devil and run and say, 'I'm not taking your package.'Symptoms come and people die.

01:15:22.792 --> 01:15:28.783
I understand that. I've seen it. But I try to get a hold of it just like that for my daughter Megan.

01:15:28.784 --> 01:15:42.262
I'm walking it out just like everybody else is. I try to say, 'God, I'm not taking the poo-poo package for Megan no more. Megan's healed. Megan's whole.

01:15:42.263 --> 01:15:56.600
Megan's well.'And I believe even in 2026 that I'm no longer going to see a daughter laying in bed all the time, that she'll be able to come on this broadcast and tell you all that I was once lost, but now I'm found.

01:15:56.601 --> 01:16:20.799
But not only that, that Jesus Christ healed me, too. Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever, and I choose to believe it. I choose to believe it.

01:16:20.800 --> 01:16:30.218
